history.text: Dicaprio is a fine actor
He is really but I think Jonah Hill deserves all the credit for this one. He acted a lot better
He stepped a bit out of his normal roles for sure
Also, I believe it was not as much as DiCaprio being a good actor. Scorsese really knows how to direct his actors. Don't you think ?
No denying that, I'm surprised the critical response is so negative on there
Me too, I quite enjoyed the movie. But Critic's soemtimes are too tough
Yeah it seems they are sometimes viewing the film in a way the average person is not.
They say the characters are dull they seem pretty lively to me. Based on true events as well.
I agree the characters were fine. I wonder how many liberties they took with truthfulness though. They often stretch that pretty far.
It was not clear for me how faithful they stayed to the book. as I did not read it.
Me neither. Didn't it win a bunch of academy awards?
I am not really sure. With these reviews it looks like it did pretty bad. What do you think of Margot Robbie's performance ?
It was good but maybe even average. I wasn't blown away for sure.
I like how he picked himself up after his first failure at Wall Street. He did a really good job at the penny stocks place.
Indeed. Penny stocks are supposed to a really tough way to get ahead.
but it was a good start for him
but he got too rich too fast and too soon .. which got him under the microscope of the FBI
He was not exactly low-key either. Odd they do not use the IMDB rating I thought it was the most popular
I mainly consider Rotten Tomatoes, they are more aligned with my taste. But do you think saying the genre is black comedy is right.
what do you think ?
Yeah it is fair to classify it as that. Biography if it sticks to the truth but comedic for sure.
but it is really weird he would marry a prostitute, he had a good thing going on with his wife .
That was his personality I think, he was reckless and pleasure seeking to bad degree.
He got off pretty light I think considering the money involved.
Were you surprised Donnie snitched?
Hello?
you there?
No not at all .. I could always see it coming
that he would snitch
I think it was very reasonable how it ended ... with him working again and doing seminars
Yeah but I am sure he owes a load of money and got lucky in my opinion.
I think the point of the movie that a hustler is always a hustler .. and will always find a way to make money
That's probably true. Also shows the level of corruption and fraud that comes with Wall Street.
